within an ECS cluster, usingn Fargate launch type to host a website
database credentials supplied using environment variables to comply with strict security compliance
ensure credentials are secure and cannot be viewed in plain text on cluster itslef

ECS enables you to inject sensitive data into containers by storing sensitive data in either AWS Secrets Manager secrets or Systems Manager parameter Store parameeters

supported by both EC2 and Frgate launch types
secrets can be exposed to a container in the following ways:
 - inject sensitive data into your containers as environemnt vatiables - use secrets container definition parameter
 - reference sensitive information in the log configuration of a container - secretOptions container definition parameter
 - within container definition, specify secrets with full name of environment variable to set in the container and full ARN of either Secrets Manager sceret or Systems Manager Parameter Store parameter containing sensitive data
 - parameter referecned can be from a different Region than the container using it, must be within the same account
 
Use AWS Systems Manager Prrameter Store to keep database credentials and then encrypt them using KMS
create an IAM Role for ECS task execution role (taskRoleARN) and reference it with your task definition - allows both KMS and Paramterer Store
Within container definition, specify secrets with the name of the environment variable to set in container and full ARN of the Systems Manager Parameter Store parameter containing sensitive data to present to continer


Docker Secrets can be used to secure sensitive database credentials, only applicable in Docker Swarm
In AWS, recommended way to secure sensitive data is to use Sedrets Manager or Systems Manager Parameter Store

Storing sensitive credentials in S3 is not recommended
a lot of overhead and manual config, simpliofied by Secrets Manager or aManager Parameter Store

ECS does not support resource-based policies, S3 does, an ECS task assumes an execution role (IAM role) to eb able to call other AWS services like Secrets Manager on your behalf
 
 








multiple apps in VPC, multiple port scans coming in from a specific IP address block, trying to connect to several AWS resources inside their VPC
security requests all IPs denied for next 24 hours

quickest and easiest method to quickly and temporarily deny access from specified IP addresses?

control VPC network by using network access control list (ACL)
optional layer of security for VPC that acts as a firewall for all traffic coming in and out of more than one subnets
can be easily added and removed


IAM policy does not control inbound and outbound traffic of your VPC

Security Group acts as a firewall, but only inbound and outbound traffic at instance level, not whole VPC

adding a firewall in the nuderlying connection is not enough, attacker can connect to another AWS resource



